title: FIFA keeps Feb. 26 election date; Platini status uncertain
text: Photo: Walter Bieri, AP FIFA Executive Committee Member Al Sabah Sheikh Ahmad Al Fahad from Kuwait arrives at the FIFA headquarters in Zurich, Switzerland, Tuesday Oct. 20, 2015. A FIFA Executive Committee meeting will take place at the Home of FIFA in Zurich. (Walter Bieri/Keystone via AP) FIFA Executive Committee Member Al Sabah Sheikh Ahmad Al Fahad from... ZURICH (AP) — FIFA decided Tuesday to stick with its presidential election date in February, as uncertainty surrounded Michel Platini's candidacy and Asia's top soccer official edged closer to entering the race. FIFA Executive Committee Member Al Sabah Sheikh Ahmad Al Fahad from Kuwait arrives at the FIFA headquarters in Zurich, Switzerland, Tuesday Oct. 20, 2015.
